comment: Redick (LAC) makes incidental contact with Diaw (SAS) that does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Green (SAS) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket and the help defending Duncan (SAS) cleanly blocks Griffin's (LAC) shot attempt in the lane.
Diaw (SAS) strips the ball from Griffin (LAC).
RATR shows that Redick's (LAC) right arm locks Parker's (SAS) left arm and affects his movement to the basket and layup attempt.
Leonard (SAS) makes contact with Griffin's (LAC) body and arms and the contact affects his movement to the basket and layup attempt.
Diaw (SAS) makes contact with the ball and does not dislodge Jordan (LAC) while going for the rebound.
Griffin (LAC) strips the ball from Duncan (SAS).
Leonard (SAS) makes contact with Barnes' (LAC) arm and the contact affects his movement to the basket and layup attempt.
Leonard (SAS) slides his pivot foot as he attempts to create space.
Paul (LAC) trips over Jordan's (LAC) feet as he attempts to get open on the inbounds pass. Leonard (SAS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Paul.
Duncan (SAS) legally contests Griffin's (LAC) running floater.
Parker (SAS) makes incidental contact with Jordan (LAC) that does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Barnes (LAC) runs through the legal screen set by Parker (SAS).
Jordan (LAC) makes contact with the ball while part of it still remains in the cylinder above the basket ring.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Jordan (LAC) committed offensive basket interference was upheld.
Griffin (LAC) commits a take foul on Green (SAS).
Paul (LAC) grabs Green's (SAS) arm and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Crawford (LAC) commits a take foul on Leonard (SAS).
